This paper discusses the problem of assessing the similarity of learned representations in neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and specifically in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of subspace match, which is a mathematical concept related to linear algebra and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for better methods of understanding learned representations, which could fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions classification tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV).
